results.name: Number of partitions of n into 4 unordered relatively prime parts.
link: Index entries for sequences related to partitions
formula: G.f.: Sum_{k>=1} mu(k)*x^(4*k) / Product_{j=1..4} (1 - x^(j*k)). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Aug 31 2019
a(n) = Sum_{k=1..floor(n/4)} Sum_{j=k..floor((n-k)/3)} Sum_{i=j..floor((n-j-k)/2)} [gcd(k,j,i,n-i-j-k) = 1], where [ ] is the Iverson bracket. - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Jan 17 2021
mathematica: Table[Sum[Sum[Sum[KroneckerDelta[GCD[k, j, i, (n - i - j - k)], 1], {i, j,  Floor[(n - j - k)/2]}], {j, k, Floor[(n - k)/3]}], {k, Floor[n/4]}], {n, 4, 80}] (* _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Jan 17 2021 *)
